    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1869-07-02T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1869-07-02T00:00:00-05:00" n="407" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d407">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Barlow</persName>,
                                    United States marshal, to Mr. <persName type="to">Hoar</persName>, Attorney-General.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <dateline>
                    <placeName>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Brooklyn, New
                                    York</hi>
                    </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1869-07-02">
                        <hi rend="italic">July</hi> 2,
                                1869</date>.</dateline>
                <p rend="flushleft">
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Attorney-General</hi>, <hi rend="italic">Washington:</hi>
                </p>
                <p>I have taken full charge of the men, according to your order of this
                                morning, and will see that they are rationed at my expense, and will
                                hold them until further orders.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>FRANCIS C. BARLOW,<lb/>
                        <hi rend="italic">United States
                                        Marshal.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
